Key Match Events: Travis Head scored 80 runs off 25 balls, including 12 fours and 5 sixes.
Mitchell Marsh scored 39 runs off 12 balls, including 5 fours and 3 sixes.
Mark Watt took 2 wickets for 13 runs in 2 overs.
Australia won the match by 7 wickets, chasing down 154 in just 9.4 overs.
Pre-Game Insights: Australia elected to bowl after winning the toss.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was held at Grange Cricket Club, Raeburn Place, Edinburgh.

Richie Richardson from West Indies was the match referee.
